textBeforeTable: For those wanting the freedom to move then car rental offers the flexibility to choose where and when to travel. Driving on the same side of the road as Australia, with wonderful scenery and possible wildlife sightings, makes this an enjoyable experience. Car Hire in South Africa     Day 10: Cape Town Drop off your rental vehicle in the morning. (B) Days 8 & 9: Cape Town Two full days at leisure to enjoy the activities and sights. (B) Day 7: Cape Town Head south to Cape Town. Three nights at FOUR ROSEMEAD, situated on the slopes of Table Mountain. (B) Day 6: Franschhoek Sample excellent South African wine or simply explore the beautiful Franschoek region. (B) Day 5: Oudthoorn – Franschhoek Today you will travel to Franschhoek in the beautiful Cape Winelands. Spend two nights at LA FONTAINE GUEST HOUSE, which offers beautiful mountain views. (B) Day 4: Oudtshoorn Head north to Oudtshoorn to visit an ostrich farm and the Cango Caves. ROSENHOF COUNTRY HOUSE. (B) Day 3: Knysna Today is yours at leisure to explore Knysna. (B) Day 2: Knysna Travel along the famous Garden Route to Knysna. Two nights at BELVIDERE MANOR. (B) Day 1: Port Elizabeth You will be met and assisted with the collection of your rental vehicle.
